        <odd id="ref22">
            <head>Early American History Not</head>
            <p>John Sellers was a prominent farmer in Upper Darby, Pennsylvania. This collection of his papers consists of a variety of documents most of which have to do with his financial and business dealings. Of particular note is a diary he kept from 1808 to 1846, which records a wide range of events. The multi-volume diary trace Sellers transition from a Philadelphian to a full-time farmer. The entries are short and detail oriented – recording visits and activities but providing little color or description beyond the basics.</p>
        </odd>
